Thorpe, property advisers, have found.
Demand fell last year because of recessionary pressures, including the fall
in town-centre rents, which removed business parks' cost advantages. The
take-up of space last year fell to 3m sq ft, a 75 per cent drop on the peak
levels in 1989.
