FT  22 JUL 93 / Parliament and Politics: Maastricht's progress
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
February 7 1992: Treaty signed
May 21 1992: European Communities (Amendment) bill secures second Commons
reading with majority of 244
June 2 1992: Danes reject treaty in referendum
September 16 1992: Sterling suspended from ERM
November 4 1992: Government wins Maastricht paving motion by three votes
December 1 1992: Commons committee stage of detailed line-by-line
consideration begins
April 22 1993: Commons rejects holding a British referendum by a majority of
239 votes
April 22 1993: Committee stage completed after 23 days and 163 hours of
debate
May 18 1993: Danes back treaty in second referendum
May 20 1993: Bill secures Commons third reading with majority of 180
July 14 1993: Lords rejects British referendum by a majority of 269 votes.
Lady Thatcher defies party three-line whip for first time in 34 years in
parliament
July 19 1993: Lord Rees-Mogg wins High Court permission to mount legal
challenge to ratification
July 20 1993: Bill secures Lords third reading by majority of 112 and
receives royal assent
July 22 1993: Commons and Lords debate the social chapter, bringing to 74
the number of Maastricht-related votes in the two houses
