<HEADLINE>
FT  22 JUL 93 / Mubarak set for third term
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By MARK NICHOLSON
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   CAIRO
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
President Hosni Mubarak of Egypt was set to win parliamentary approval last
night to run unopposed for a third six-year term as the country's leader,
Mark Nicholson writes from Cairo. The vote is a formality since 98 per cent
of the People's Assembly's 454 elected members have already sworn their
support for his nomination.
His nomination must then be endorsed by a referendum in October, when he
will need a simple majority of votes cast. This too is expected to be little
more than a formality; he secured 97 per cent of the vote last time.
</TEXT>
