FT  21 JUL 93 / International Company News: Long distance calls help Sprint
up 58%
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By MARTIN DICKSON
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
SPRINT, the US telecommunications group, yesterday reported a 58 per cent
increase in second-quarter net income from continuing operations, thanks to
strong growth in its long distance operating income.
Reported income from continuing operations was Dollars 165m, or 48 cents a
share, compared with Dollars 104m, or 31 cents, a year earlier. This
excludes a Dollars 44m, or 13 cents a share, after-tax gain it made last
year from the sale of telephone properties in Ohio. Its revenues rose 9 per
cent to Dollars 2.8bn.
Net income totalled Dollars 157m, or 46 cents, compared with Dollars 148m,
or 44 cents.
Sprint, the third-largest long distance carrier in the US, said this
business saw operating income of Dollars 121m, compared with Dollars 45m
last time.
Revenues rose 10 per cent to Dollars 1.51bn, compared with Dollars 1.38bn a
year ago and Dollars 1.49bn in the first quarter. Minutes of use rose 9 per
cent on a year ago.
