<HEADLINE>
FT  21 JUL 93 / International Company News: Cincinnati Milacron doubles
income
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ANDREW BAXTER
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
CINCINNATI MILACRON, the US machine tools and plastics machinery group,
yesterday announced more than doubled second-quarter operating earnings, but
expressed concern about the condition of US and European economies.
Operating net rose from Dollars 2.77m, or 10 cents a share, to Dollars
5.83m, or 18 cents. The latest figure excludes a Dollars 4.4m charge for
early extinguishment of debt, while the 1992 figure excludes a Dollars
700,000 gain from a loss carry-forward.
For the first six months, operating net earnings jumped from Dollars 3.88m,
or 14 cents a share, to Dollars 10.1m, or 33 cents. However, the latest
figure excludes both the Dollars 4.4m charge and a charge of Dollars 52.1m
for accounting changes. The 1992 figure excludes a Dollars 900,000 gain from
carry-forwards.
Revenues jumped from Dollars 185.6m to Dollars 237.2m in the latest quarter,
taking the six-month total to Dollars 458.2m, against Dollars 345.6m.
Mr Daniel Meyer, chairman, said Milacron's first-half results were on
target.
</TEXT>
