term expired in March, Baroness James, the novelist and Keith Oates,
managing director of Marks and Spencer, whose terms run out at the end of
this month.
Two further governors have to be appointed to bring the board up to full
strength.
Lord Cocks, MP for Bristol South from 1970-1987, will receive an annual
salary of Pounds 14,715 for the part-time job. The other governors get
Pounds 7,360.
