modern age, access to the telephone is as important as access to the postal
service.'
BT welcomed Labour's support for an end to the entertainment ban, which it
claims is anti-competitive and a hindrance to its capacity to finance an
advanced fibre-optic network within local exchanges. It refused to concede
the need for further reductions in connection charges to increase lines.
Last month the cost of installing a phone line was reduced from Pounds 152
to Pounds 99, cut to Pounds 36.78 for those taking over an existing exchange
line and set at zero for those doing so immediately the previous occupant
has moved.
