<HEADLINE>
FT  21 JUL 93 / Parliament and Politics: MPs slam funding of London's
railways
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By RICHARD TOMKINS
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
THE Commons transport committee yesterday delivered a strongly worded
warning that underground and rail services in London would rapidly decline
without a big increase in investment, Richard Tomkins writes.
In a report on transport investment in the capital, MPs said they had
received clear evidence from both Network SouthEast and London Underground
that present levels of investment were insufficient to maintain or improve
the transport system.
They acknowledged that investment in London's transport in the past few
years had been higher than in previous decades, but said earlier
under-investment had 'heaped up trouble' for the future.
The report recommended a government commitment to a sustained and higher
level of investment.
London's Public Transport Capital Investment Requirements. Transport
Committee. HoC Paper 754. HMSO. Pounds 14.40.
