<HEADLINE>
FT  20 JUL 93 / International Capital Markets: Mortgage bond issue by Banco
Santander
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By TRACY CORRIGAN
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
BANCO Santander, the Spanish bank, has launched a Pta13.5bn issue of
mortgage-backed bonds in the Spanish market, the first under Spain's new
securitisation law which has clarified tax problems facing issuers of
mortgage-backed debt.
Banco Santander had already issued two mortgage-backed deals under the
previous law, using a different structure.
The bonds have a semi-annual coupon of 10 1/4 per cent and mature on June 30
2010, but are expected to have an average life of 5.7 years. The mortgage
loans represent 47.15 per cent of the current value of the properties on
which they are secured.
The bonds are rated AA by Iberating, Standard &amp; Poor's Spanish subsidiary.
